      "writtenOn": "2017-11-22T17:24:07Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Now that you bring it up I see how this is awkward.\n\nThe point of passing in all points was because we can now, and because SkClassifyCubic requires an array of all 4. So this saves us the need to create an intermediate array that contains P0 inside of cubicTo.\n\nDo you think it would be better for code clarity to just take the three and accept the cost of making an intermediate array?",
